<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/563000072/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """Progressive Evaluation:
Assistance to Laboratory Practices. Weight: 0% of the final grade. Students must attend at least 80% of the practical classes. This activity is not recoverable.
CourseWorks. Weight: 50% of the final mark. Students will deliver the results of the 5 courseworks that are carried out in the subject within the period set by their practice teacher. The final mark of the courseworks is obtained as indicated below.
Mc = 0.15*mc1+0.25*mc2+0.15*mc3+0.25*mc4+0,20*mc5, where mc1, mc2, mc3, mc4 and mc5 is the mark of each of the 5 courseworks, each evaluated on 10 points. The courseworks delivered after the deadline set by the teacher of practices will be graded with a 0. No minimum mark is required.
Global Test: Weight: 50% of the final mark. It consists in an individual written test that will contain short questions, demostrations, practical cases and/or numerical exercises. There will also be an individual test that will be done by computer consisting of practical cases similar to those made in the laboratory. The Global Written test is mandatory. A minimum grade of 4.0 points out of 10 is required.
The final grade for the course is obtained as follows:
M = 0.5*Mc+0.5*Mgw, where Mgwt is the mark obtained in the Global Written Test.
To pass the subject it will be necessary to have attended at least 80% of the practical classes, obtain a mark equal to or greater than 4.0 points out of 10 in the global written test and that the final mark of the subject is equal to or greater than 5 points out of 10.


Extraordinary Call:
For the extraordinary call, students will take an exam, that will contain short short questions, demonstrations, practical cases and/or numerical exercises. There will also be an individual test that will be done by computer consisting of practical cases similar to those made in the laboratory. . The final mark will be the one obtained in this exam and will have a 100% weight on the final marke.
To pass the subject it will be necessary to have attended at least 80% of the practical classes and a mark equal to or greater than 5 points out of 10 in the written exam."""@es ;
